7.00	British_absolute_block_signalling	British absolute block signalling	The principle of the British absolute block system of railway signalling is to ensure the safe operation of a railway by allowing only one train to occupy a defined section of track at a time. This system is used on double or multiple lines where use of each line is assigned a direction of travel.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b9/Block_instrument.jpg/250px-Block_instrument.jpg
